Description: Diademed head of Ptolemy I with aegis, right. (obverse)
Eagle standing on thunderbolt with wings closed, left; to left L Κ Α; to right, Π Α. (reverse)
Curator's comments: This coin appears to be a contemporary forgery. Though made in base metal, it imitates the silver type and appears originally to have been silver plated. Another example was found at Tell el Farain in 1968 (BM C&M 2009,4181.53).
